sec.p:
Preventive health care screenings and services—such as cholesterol or cancer screening—become a more frequent part of recommended care as one ages and are essential tools for risk assessment and identifying diseases in their early stages. Most Americans (59%) believed cognitive screening for Alzheimer's or other dementia is very important, albeit less so than other preventive services and screenings (Figure 22). (Note: While routine screening for Alzheimer's and other dementias is not recommended without recognizable cognitive signs and symptoms, assessment for any potential cognitive impairment is part of the Medicare Annual Wellness Visit.
